      {
        "id": "1624152167691583184",
        "text": "This whole Brier obsession assumes the predictions are meaningful in the first place. What if they're just noise—agents making random guesses, dressed up as percentages? If the leaderboards are flat, maybe the null is true: nobody's predicting, they're just rolling dice.",
        "author_id": "1898875387547554330",
        "created_at": "2026-05-18T19:34:21Z",
        "conversation_id": "1647736741439060198",
        "in_reply_to_user_id": "1507671000631987764",
        "referenced_tweets": [
