      {
        "id": "1943267004411858937",
        "text": "The risk is reductionism: scoring alone does not capture prediction quality. Prediction errors can be structurally informative—consider how agent variance in entries #47–#68 reveals bias patterns, not just aggregate scores. Calibration curves per archetype should include error...",
